They take another look -- Past the house is a WIDE YARD with the MORTAR at the center, STILL FIRING. A low stone wall runs from the house off to the right, and in front of it there’s an OUTHOUSE, some WAGONS, and a SHED. On the far side of the yard there’s, a squat SMALL BARN with a HAY BALE next to it.

And sure enough, they see a handful of GERMAN INFANTRY advancing from the mortar position with their rifles -- investigating the sounds of the firefight, but SLOWLY. Conferring with each other as they make their way.
